{
  "texts": [
    "A blockchain provides a distributed database of transactions that every node on the network can access, also referred to as a digital ledger (Nofer et al. 2017).",
    "The network is a collection of hardware (such as computers) that must all approve a transaction for it to be validated and recorded.",
    "Transactions can also be easily audited by all the relevant parties.",
    "A BC is merely a data format that enables the creation and distribution of an exchanges \"tamper-proof digital ledger\".",
    "Therefore, compared to centralized systems, BC systems can make transactions more safe and transparent."
  ]
}